  "paragraphs": [
    {
      "para_id": "Q004253.1",
      "line_range": "1",
      "translation": "(1) At the time when Lugal-ayaĝu , the temple administrator of Iškur , ruled in Adab , Damgalnuna chose Ur-Imma in her holy heart and told him “Build my temple for me!” , and after Ur-Imma had gone to Damgalnuna to tell her of his intentions , Ur-Imma , the powerful house-born slave of Damgalnuna , the powerful servant of Imma , the powerful descendant of Lugal-niĝbarag-dug’s clan , excavated ( her temple's ) 6 kuš and 1 zapah deep foundation pit . He assigned a nueša priest , a cupbearer , male and female servants to the temple ."
    },
    {
      "para_id": "Q004253.24",
      "line_range": "24",
      "translation": "(24) Because of these , Damgalnuna decided a good fate for Ur-Imma , and ( when ) he requested from her the well-being of his mother , the well-being of his spouse and child , and the well-being his brothers , ( then ) Damgalnuna stood by him in this ."
    }
  ],
